pageContext.claim: “African-American unemployment has recently achieved the lowest rate ever recorded. What do you have to lose? What do you have to lose?”
pageContext.analysis: The black and Hispanic unemployment rates have been calculated only since 1972, so it's an exaggeration to say the current numbers are the lowest in history. The U.S. jobless rate for Asians has been around for less than 20 years. Although the black unemployment rate was at an all-time-low 5.9 percent in May, it had risen to 6 percent in September. That was still significantly higher than the overall unemployment rate of 3.7 percent.
